private final RateLimiter rateLimiter = RateLimiter.create(1000.0 / DatabaseDescriptor.getCDCDiskCheckInterval());
```
This `rateLimiter` is then applied in `recalculateOverflowSize()`:
```java
private void recalculateOverflowSize()
{
    rateLimiter.acquire();
    calculateSize();
    // ...
}
```
The `calculateSize()` method performs a potentially expensive `Files.walkFileTree` operation to sum the sizes of files in the CDC directory. By using the `rateLimiter` based on `cdc_disk_check_interval_ms`, the system ensures that these disk-intensive recalculations do not occur more frequently than the configured interval, even if multiple requests for recalculation are submitted (e.g., via `submitOverflowSizeRecalculation()`). This prevents excessive I/O overhead from frequent directory scans.

